{
  "stem": "7414.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the fact the money that he-- she, for example, earned from a patient, she bought a beautiful coat for my baby, [LAUGHS] not that this.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Look, of course it was under German occupation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Poles did not have it easy themselves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First of all, if it comes to food, and secondly, the resistance.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every time that they did something to the Germans, the-- the Germans were punishing them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was there, for example, once with the baby in the pram when they closed both sides of a street, I just had time enough to run with the pram under this-- how you call this, iron shutters-- under the iron shutter to a shop.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they closed, and they gathered every men which was in the street, you see, and they send them off.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most probably they said that is how the son of my Aunt Paula was caught.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They sent them over to Auschwitz or to other camps, or they.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Once I saw, when I walked in the street, a row Polish people hanging from the balcony as a punishment for some deed which they did.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that did not stop them to hand over the Jews to the German, see?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, we are at home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I am living the normal life, going out, going shopping, cooking, and going-- every few days, I had to go to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was on the other part of Warsaw because I got there a bottle of mother's milk for my baby.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I could not with a pram to go on a train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was walking back, like from here, for example, to the-- this-- the bridge and back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And back.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, what I could do, I was-- I had to do it.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
